			<div class='post_body'>
				<p class='posted_info desc lighter ipsType_small'>
					Posted <abbr class="published" itemprop="commentTime" title="2014-03-02T04:56:15+00:00">01 March 2014 - 11:56 PM</abbr>
					
				</p>
				
				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					Note that open_basedir won't prevent someone from reading another users files if you still allow things like exec()/system() as they could just use those to get around the restriction.<br><br>If you are using PHP-FPM one thing you can do is setup a separate pool for each user and set the chroot directive to lock them into their home directory. There wouldn't be any way the user could get around that restriction.
					
					<br />
					
				</div>
				
				
